This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with face restoration, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of ensemble learning and sequential gating units also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category as it deals with image restoration, and the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it uses neural networks for its approach.
